\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Trigger Logic
\f0\b0 \uc0\u8232 When the LLM flags a significant negative signal for a major holding or sector\'97say, a regulatory investigation or negative earnings surprise\'97a conditional trigger initiates a targeted rebalance. For example, if the predicted probability of a \'93very negative\'94 event exceeds 70%, sector weights can be trimmed or hedged immediately, rather than waiting for price drift thresholds.\
